olonial assimilation to the economic crisis in West Africa and the attacks on Haiti, Liberia, and Ethiopia, On the Scale of the World shows how counternarratives of global order enabled original ways of thinking about race, nation, and empire.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Black Studies (Global).2bisacsh  aBlack political thought.  aactivism.  aafrica.  aafrican.  aamerica.  aamerican.  aanticolonial.  aanticolonialism.  aassimilation.  abritish.  acaribbean.  acolonialism.  aempire.  afrance.  afrench.  aghana.  aliterary.  anation.  anigeria.  arace.  asierra leone.  astates.  astudies.  aunited.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishz978311099455108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022z9783110994520oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076649340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520389175?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520389175423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520389175/original  a978-3-11-076649-3  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099455-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DSLb2022  aZDB-23-UCY